spanGrp.span: They came to work… to work planting beans, corn and rice.
Jie-wa betẽũ-lo-te rö shkablö shakblö (_) kenĩ kenĩ wökbö kuö tkö arros tkö
But they never thought they would stay and live here.
Tara jie-wa ka *të [wã] í begetse-nẽ ke jie-wa jatanã-mĩ jiska sẽ-nã'
How many lived, worked and grew up here!
(_) Bikö jie-wa sẽ-nã' jie-wa shkablá jie-wa kebi-nã'
Their children were born and got married here.
Jie-wa yabla kõ-nã' jie-wa juepe-wa yulá jiska
they lived … uh… they worked and got married.
jie-wa sẽ-nã' de jie-wa shkablá (eh) ñã jula gugá
They made a road that goes all the way to Buenos Aires.
Jie-wa të të ñala yuá-nẽ rö de dömĩ Buenos Aires
They saw that here is a nice place to live.
jie-wa të sũã-ra ke jiska ka rö bá se sẽ-nã-glö
they say that they came to live here; they work for the [white] people, if they pay them well;
jie-wa të jie-wa të she Jie-wa të (_) (_) të pe ĩã shkablö-gẽ pe të í patuẽ-gẽ böi ra
actually they don’t, but anyway, they remained living here.
ka rö böi bueno (m) pero jie-wa jata-nã' sẽ-nã' jiska
